Products.FullDescription: Calippo Mini Water Ice Raspberry & Pineapple
Products.RichDescription:
CALIPPO MINI WATER ICE RASPBERRY PINEAPPLE MP10 575 ML

SAY GOODBYE SERIOUS, HELLO JOY. Calippo Mini’s in Raspberry and Pineapple flavour! Great for a refreshing snack at home, enjoy your two favourite fruit flavours combined together into the one miniature block! All contain 25% real fruit juices as well as being 99% fat free. Conveniently in a miniature format, these are perfect for the family to share in a 10 pack. Enjoy the great juicy taste of Calippo, the taste you love and so refreshing! Using real fruit juice, Calippo is perfect for the summer heat or an evening snack. Between WWI and WWII, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted Street. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one horse power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well known brands such as Magnum, Paddle Pop, Cornetto, Gaytime, Calippo and Blue Ribbon.

25% Fruit Juice

99% Fat Free

Great Juicy Taste

Raspberry Pineapple

Delicious

Refreshingly fruity

Steggles Crumbed Chicken Breast Nuggets make dinner quick & tasty! Free from artificial colours or flavours with good source of protein. Our chickens have no added hormones.

- All Steggles chickens are raised in large barns and are free from any added hormones.

Products.Name: Streets Cornetto Golden Gaytime
Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Streets Cornetto Golden Gaytime' has a supply limit of 36. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.RichDescription:
CORNETTO ICE CONFECTION GAYTIME 440 ML
SAY GOODBYE SERIOUS, HELLO JOY. Introducing the ultimate food love-child Cornetto Golden Gaytime! Your favourite Gaytime is now in a delicious wafer cone with a choc tip and biscuit crumbs sprinkled on top! Now with improved chocolatey crunch, Gaynetto is perfect for a refreshing snack at home or to share with friends and family. Everyone knows you can’t have a Gaytime on your own!! Between World War 1 and World War 2, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted Street. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one horse power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well known brands such as Magnum, Paddle Pop, Cornetto, Gaytime, Calippo and Blue Ribbon. Gaytime was first created in 1959, although it wasn’t until 1970 that Golden Gaytime was released, becoming an Aussie icon in the process!
Gaytime flavoured treat
Wafer cone
Chocolatey tip
Gaytime crumbs
Cornetto and Gaytime finally together
Delicious treat!

Products.RichDescription:
Coco & Lucas' Beef Cottage Pie is lovingly hand made.

I was given this gorgeous recipe by my good friend Gitta and it's now one of my family's favourites! Gitta has fond memories of her mother cooking this for her and her sisters when they were growing up in Kilkenny, Ireland. With warm, fluffy potato mash, topped with tasty cheddar cheese, baked with lean mince, cooked in yummy beef gravy, hand-cut mushrooms, corn, peas and carrots - this dish is bound to please!

Coco & Lucas' Story.

As a mother of two young children I created Coco & Lucas' hand made meals to help families like my own, who want quality, home-cooked meals, but don't always have the time to create them. Our children are precious and every mouthful is carefully crafted to give them the wholesome nourishment they need.

Ideal for junior foodies. 3-12 year olds.

No artificial preservatives, flavours or colours.

Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen
Bbq Pork Buns 200g
Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen Bbq Pork Buns' has a supply limit of 5. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.SmallFormatDescription: Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen Bbq Pork Buns
Products.FullDescription: Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen Bbq Pork Buns
Products.RichDescription:
Our BBQ Pork Buns are a Yum Cha classic - consisting of a light and fluffy bun stuffed with roasted Char Siu pork and our signature, smoky sauce. Simply steam for 10 minutes and the buns are ready!

For the filling, we receive fresh, Australian pork shoulder every day which we trim and marinate before roasting in our in-house furnace. The open flame produces a crispy, velvet exterior whilst being juicy and packed with flavour on the inside. Our sauce is also made from scratch and has a rich, savoury taste designed to enhance the flavour of roasted Char Siu Pork.

Unlike steamed bun recipes which require yeast as a rising agent, we use a traditional fermentation method when making our bun dough - allowing it to rise for 24-hours. The result is a fluffy and pillowy texture and a hearty aroma when steamed.

Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen has been proudly making Dim Sum in Australia since 1982. Our vision is to maintain and promote the integrity of authentic Dim Sum for all families to enjoy.

Products.RichDescription:
Our Pork Dim Sims are the ultimate comfort food. Made with fresh Australian pork mince and cabbage, we have the belief that the better the ingredients, the less fuss that needs to be done to it. As you bite into each Dim Sim, you can expect a full-bodied texture, juiciness and hearty flavour that can only be achieved by using quality Australian pork. 

Whether you’ve just gotten home from a long day at work , having a weekend BBQ, or preparing lunch for the kids, place a few Dim Sims in the steamer and you have yourself a meal that is super easy, delicious, and a good source of protein with over 8 grams per 100g! For a more delectable serving suggestion, lightly fry the Dim Sims after heating for a snack that is golden and crunchy on the outside, and juicy and meaty on the inside. 

Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen has been proudly making Dim Sum in Australia since 1982. Our vision is to maintain and promote the integrity of authentic Dim Sum for all families to enjoy.
